]

instance fidelity_and_validity_considerations : DTDFVocab:FidelityConsideration [
    base:desc "Model fidelity is ensured by a validation service that periodically compares the real‑time encoder measurements with the kinematic model predictions; deviations beyond 2 % trigger an error‑correction routine. The analytical model is calibrated using recorded data from the InfluxDB store, and uncertainty is quantified by propagating sensor tolerance (±0.5 %) through the simulation. Continuous integration tests verify model‑data consistency before each VM image release, providing quality assurance for both models and data."
]

instance dt_technical_connection : DTDFVocab:TechnicalConnection [
    base:desc "The digital‑twin services communicate through an MQTT broker that acts as a central signaling hub. All containers (Trajectory Generator Service, Simulation Service, Continuous Validation Service, Dashboard, etc.) publish and subscribe to MQTT topics over TCP/IP. No further details on bandwidth, latency, topology, redundancy or security protocols are provided in the documents."
